Create a class called Employee inside the package in.mindcraft.

It should have the following instance variables:
String empName
int empId
double salary

Define two methods:
displayInfo() → prints employee details.
setEmployeeDetails(String name, int id, double salary) → uses this keyword 
to set values and calls displayInfo().

In the main method of the TestEmployee class:

Create two Employee objects.
One object will use default values.
Another object will use setEmployeeDetails() to set custom values.



class Employee
      String empName="Sujal";
      int empId=21;
      double salary=1234;
      void displayInfo() {
	  System.out.println("empName:"+empName+"empId:"+ empId+"salary:"+salary);
      }
      void displayInfoUsingParameter(String name,int age,double salary) {
  		this.empName=empName;
  		this.empId=empId;
  		this.salary=salary;
  		displayInfo();
  	}
}



package in.mindcraft;

public class TestEmployee {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		Employee emp1=new Employee();
		emp1.displayInfo();
		Employee emp2=new Employee ();
		emp2.displayInfoUsingParameter("Amit",98,12355);

	}

}
